# AI Runtime API — use with REST Client (VS Code extension: REST Client by Huachao Mao)
# Click "Send Request" above a request block, or use the shortcut.

@base = http://localhost:3000
@workflowId = <paste workflowId from start response>

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Workflows (run worker:customer-support for customerSupport, worker:research-assistant for contentBrief)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Start customer-support workflow
POST {{base}}/workflows/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workflowType": "customerSupport",
  "input": {
    "message": "I want a refund for my order",
    "orderId": "ORD-123"
  }
}

### Start content-brief workflow (research-assistant worker)
POST {{base}}/workflows/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workflowType": "contentBrief",
  "input": {
    "topic": "Sustainable packaging in e-commerce",
    "audience": "B2B"
  }
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Agents (customer-support: travelAgent | research-assistant: researchAssistant)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Start travel agent
POST {{base}}/agents/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agentName": "travelAgent",
  "input": {
    "message": "Search for flights from NYC to London on March 15th."
  }
}

### Start research assistant
POST {{base}}/agents/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agentName": "researchAssistant",
  "input": {
    "message": "What is the latest news on the war in Iran?"
  }
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Runs (use workflowId from start response)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Get run status
GET {{base}}/runs/{{workflowId}}

### Get run result (wait until status is COMPLETED)
GET {{base}}/runs/{{workflowId}}/result
